The opening weekend of the new Premier League season saw some terrific goals scored, but none quite matched that of Arminia Bielefeld striker Fabian Klos.

The 26-year-old  hit the back of the net with arguably the most eye-catching strike in all of European football on Sunday when he connected with a volley against Sandhausen.

Klos' effort, which came when he sweetly caught a floated corner with his right foot in the 57th minute, putting his side 2-0 up in the first round of the German Cup.

