Bielefeld, who play in the second division in Germany, went on to win the game 4-1, but their victory will be remembered for Klos' stunning strike.

Although it was with his right foot and not his left, Klos' goal evoked memories of Zinedine Zidane's brilliant volley in the 2002 Champions League final against Bayer Leverkusen.

The Frenchman's effort turned out to be the winner for Real Madrid, who beat the German side 2-1 at Hampden Park in Glasgow. 

